31:39.297 --> 31:39.658
I help.

31:39.738 --> 31:40.479
I do the laundry.

31:40.619 --> 31:42.421
I'm very involved in that kind of stuff.

31:42.562 --> 31:45.906
I'm domestically educated so I can do that kind of stuff.

31:46.210 --> 31:48.573
and I come alongside and I'm a helper in that way.

31:48.733 --> 31:49.294
Absolutely.

31:49.834 --> 32:06.114
As a matter of fact, I'll tell you right now, I have a 17 year old and a 16 year old daughter and if you're around that age and you're interested in my daughter, you better know how to do dishes and you better know how to do laundry because my daughters expect a future husband that's actually going to be a teammate with them and not someone who sits on their bum in a lazy chair and doesn't do anything.

32:06.454 --> 32:07.896
Sorry, that's not in my message.

32:07.956 --> 32:10.639
It just came out.

32:10.659 --> 32:11.180
It just came out.

32:11.620 --> 32:11.941
Sorry.

32:12.401 --> 32:13.042
But here's the deal.

32:14.018 --> 32:18.445
Women are equal to men in value and worth in meaning and in purpose.

32:18.886 --> 32:19.447
Absolutely.

32:19.487 --> 32:22.011
So don't read that verse incorrectly, okay?

32:22.031 --> 32:23.153
Now, let's go on, okay?

32:23.714 --> 32:29.804
So the Lord God formed from the ground all the wild animals and all the birds of the sky, and He brought them to the man to see what He would call them.

32:30.245 --> 32:31.707
And the man chose a name for each one.

32:31.747 --> 32:35.593
He gave the names to all the livestock, all the birds of the sky, and all the wild animals.

32:35.633 --> 32:37.557
What a fine process that must have been.

32:38.218 --> 32:40.882
But still, there is no helper just right for Him.

32:41.506 --> 32:43.730
So the Lord God caused the man to fall into a deep sleep.

32:43.770 --> 32:49.779
And while the man slept, the Lord took out one of the man's ribs and closed up the opening.

32:50.640 --> 32:51.161
And then the Lord...

32:51.181 --> 32:52.163
So he did surgery, right?

32:52.303 --> 32:52.684
On Adam.

32:53.144 --> 32:56.930
And then the Lord God made a woman from that rib and He brought her to the man.

32:57.611 --> 33:00.035
Verse 23, at last the man...

33:00.296 --> 33:03.441
Some translations translate that word at last.

33:03.861 --> 33:04.462
Wow!

33:04.602 --> 33:06.866
That's what it literally says.

33:07.106 --> 33:08.629
God, this is awesome.

33:08.709 --> 33:09.490
Thank you so much.

33:09.530 --> 33:11.574
She's so much better than an aardvark.

33:11.614 --> 33:12.776
God, this is awesome.

33:14.900 --> 33:18.126
And he goes on, this one is bone on my bone, flesh on my flesh.

33:18.146 --> 33:20.510
She will be called woman because she was taken out of man.

33:21.512 --> 33:22.714
But here's the thing we've got to see.

33:23.476 --> 33:26.642
We've got to see that relationships were God's idea.

33:28.385 --> 33:29.206
He engineered them.

33:30.128 --> 33:31.250
It was his idea.

33:32.962 --> 33:40.129
Verse 24, this explains why man leaves his father and mother and is joined to his wife and the two are united into one.

33:41.411 --> 33:44.233
Now the man and his wife were both naked and they felt no shame.

33:45.575 --> 33:46.135
Why is that?

33:47.116 --> 33:51.741
Because there is nothing to hide, nothing to run from, there is no fear.

33:52.262 --> 33:52.522
Why?

33:52.942 --> 33:55.725
Because they were doing relationship God's way.

33:58.408 --> 34:00.530
Think about a typical romantic comedy.

34:00.834 --> 34:03.137
This morning, you know, last week was all about adventure.

34:03.157 --> 34:04.438
Today is all about romantic comedy.

34:04.458 --> 34:06.641
Think about your typical plot of a romantic comedy.

34:06.901 --> 34:18.234
Couple meets, couple realizes they're attracted to each other, couple dates, the couple has sex, couple has drama, they break up, couple gets back together and they live happily together forever.

34:18.795 --> 34:19.656
No issues whatsoever.

34:21.818 --> 34:25.202
Notice what verse 24 of Genesis chapter 2 does not say.

34:26.242 --> 34:33.713
This explains why a teenage or young adult guy tries to have sex with as many people as he possibly can.

34:33.753 --> 34:34.754
24 doesn't actually say that.

34:36.296 --> 34:43.907
Genesis 2.24 doesn't say, this explains why a teenage or young adult girl has sex with a guy because she thinks her soul will be filled by him.

34:47.412 --> 34:50.937
This explains why people shack up with each other and then pretend it's no big deal.

34:53.621 --> 34:54.322
Doesn't say that.

34:55.650 --> 35:02.640
Nor does it not say or nor does it say this explains why people live together so they can check it out before they actually commit to it.

35:03.461 --> 35:05.945
Now, can I just say God is not embarrassed by sex.

35:06.145 --> 35:07.407
He created sex.

35:08.328 --> 35:09.250
It was his idea.

35:09.310 --> 35:10.952
He's not approved.

35:11.954 --> 35:23.250
He designed physical intimacy, but he designed it to be experienced within the relationship that he engineered for it to be experienced within.

35:24.578 --> 35:28.002
Our society celebrates sex as if it's everything.

35:28.743 --> 35:34.009
We have one night stands and we shack up and then we sack the relationship or we have an affair.

35:34.309 --> 35:36.973
And the only person that we ultimately heard is ourselves.

35:39.155 --> 35:45.563
As teens and young adults in 2021, we give up the gift of virginity way too easily today.

35:46.344 --> 35:49.027
We trash our virginity instead of treasuring it.

35:50.609 --> 35:51.890
It's something to be treasured.

35:55.810 --> 35:57.111
Very quiet in this room.

35:58.173 --> 36:02.597
He's talking about sex, virginity from stage.

36:04.880 --> 36:09.605
Our society talks about sex everywhere, on every commercial and every situation.

36:09.645 --> 36:13.730
If we can't talk about a church and God's designed for it, what is wrong with us?

36:15.311 --> 36:15.632
Sorry.

36:17.774 --> 36:18.515
Actually, not sorry.

36:20.477 --> 36:21.438
Now, can I just say this?

36:22.940 --> 36:24.882
Some of you right now in this moment

36:26.082 --> 36:29.445
You are feeling so much guilt and so much condemnation in this moment.

36:30.226 --> 36:37.673
Can I tell you, God is an amazingly loving and forgiving God, and He can make you whole again.

36:39.395 --> 36:55.090
So if you've made mistakes in the sexual area of your life, there's a God who's crazy in love with you and who invites you in to a sense and a feeling of being fully, fully embraced by His love.

36:57.026 --> 36:58.528
Do not feel condemned.

37:00.390 --> 37:06.456
Feel invited into a relationship with Almighty God who wants you to experience.

37:06.496 --> 37:07.417
Because here's the deal.

37:08.739 --> 37:14.084
Our society pretends as if sex is gonna fill up your soul, it will not fill up your soul.

37:15.526 --> 37:17.288
God fills up your soul.

37:18.890 --> 37:20.011
Sex can't.

37:22.113 --> 37:23.174
It can't fill up your soul.

37:24.355 --> 37:26.738
It was never designed by the engineer to do that.

37:27.906 --> 37:28.406
Bless you.

37:30.528 --> 37:34.472
That engineer of that expensive Lamborghini would say, you know what?

37:34.612 --> 37:35.954
The problem is not with the car.

37:36.494 --> 37:40.198
The problem is that the car was misused in the same way.

37:42.500 --> 37:43.841
The problem is not with sex.

37:43.861 --> 37:47.545
The problem is where sex is expressed in our society.

37:48.526 --> 37:53.150
Again, Adam says, wow, this one is bone for my bone and flesh for my flesh.

37:54.711 --> 37:55.372
But here's the deal.

37:55.652 --> 37:57.394
God does not want the wow.

37:57.538 --> 37:58.560
to become foul.

38:01.346 --> 38:02.849
Chris, you're not aligned with society.

38:03.249 --> 38:04.532
You got your head in the sand, bro.

38:05.694 --> 38:06.496
No, you know what I do?

38:06.777 --> 38:10.324
I actually have my head in God's Word because God's Word is truth.

38:11.827 --> 38:17.458
And God's Word is the thing that tells us where there's joy and abundance

38:18.146 --> 38:20.829
where we can experience true soul satisfaction.

38:21.149 --> 38:26.235
And God's heart for you is that you would experience absolute soul satisfaction.

38:26.436 --> 38:29.399
Again, I've got a 17-year-old and a 16-year-old daughter at home.

38:30.040 --> 38:30.580
I get this.

38:30.740 --> 38:31.561
I'm living through this.

38:31.642 --> 38:35.005
I'm watching every guy very carefully right now.

38:36.888 --> 38:41.152
I'm watching them very carefully, because I know, because I used to be 17 years old.

38:41.213 --> 38:42.514
I know what's going through their head.

38:43.298 --> 38:46.262
I also know, and again, this is not a pride thing.

38:47.043 --> 38:48.464
I got married as a virgin.

38:50.066 --> 38:56.214
Not because I'm some heroic person, but simply because I wanted to honor God with that area of my life.

38:57.716 --> 39:04.604
And I'm telling my girls, if He really loves you, then man, He will treat you with respect.

39:05.926 --> 39:06.787
I heard about a dad.

39:06.947 --> 39:07.448
I heard about a dad.

39:07.468 --> 39:08.048
This is a true story.

39:08.068 --> 39:08.689
It's a very true story.

39:08.709 --> 39:09.490
I heard about a dad.

39:10.178 --> 39:19.013
And someone was dating his teenage daughter, and so he made an appointment with her, with this guy, with the guy that was dating his teenage daughter, asked him to come to his office.

39:19.033 --> 39:28.530
So the guy came to his office, 17-year-old kid who he wanted to date his daughter, came to his office, and the dad made him wait out in the reception area for like 15 minutes, just a sweat.

39:29.826 --> 39:31.548
And it finally brought the kid in.

39:31.588 --> 39:39.578
The kid came into his office and the dad looked across the table from him and said, I just want you to know, this is not a conversation for us to become best buds.

39:39.598 --> 39:40.579
That's not what this is about.

39:42.322 --> 39:48.609
I've done the research and less than one and a half percent of people that date in high school actually go on to get married.

39:48.950 --> 39:54.677
So I'm just wondering, how are you planning to treat my daughter who's going to be someone else's wife?

39:54.877 --> 39:55.538
I'm just wondering.

39:59.714 --> 40:01.236
I'm going to use that.

40:01.717 --> 40:02.378
I'm going to use that.

40:05.422 --> 40:17.039
It may not align with society norms, but it does align with God's best for us because He engineered us.

40:18.541 --> 40:22.126
See, God says in Isaiah 55-8, my thoughts are nothing like your thoughts, says the Lord.

40:22.166 --> 40:24.550
My ways are far beyond anything you could imagine.

40:25.812 --> 40:27.474
And again, I've already referenced it.

40:28.322 --> 40:33.749
I know the plans I have for you, says the Lord, they're plans for good and not for disaster to give you a future and a hope.

40:33.769 --> 40:37.053
Now, one more thing about romantic comedies, and that's this.

40:37.713 --> 40:39.716
Every relationship takes work.

40:40.276 --> 40:44.782
Where two or three are gathered, eventually there's going to be conflict, right?

40:44.802 --> 40:46.504
It is not a question of whether or not.

40:46.544 --> 40:52.331
How many of you have been married more than a day and you haven't had any conflict in your marriage?

40:52.391 --> 40:52.932
Anybody in the room?

40:54.814 --> 40:56.857
Because if you raise your hand right now, you're lying.

40:56.937 --> 40:58.098
I'm just saying, you're lying.

40:58.242 --> 40:58.924
And you're in church.

41:00.928 --> 41:01.109
Okay?

41:01.389 --> 41:10.030
The only question is, will I allow the tension between either a marriage relationship or a co-working relationship or a relationship with a friendship or whatever?

41:10.050 --> 41:14.199
Will I allow the tension to make me better or bitter?

41:15.482 --> 41:15.582
Ah!

41:15.783 --> 41:17.106
This is a whole message in itself.

41:17.218 --> 41:18.540
that I don't have time to give this morning.

41:18.560 --> 41:19.801
But here's the thing.

41:19.821 --> 41:20.242
Here's the thing.

41:20.282 --> 41:27.472
Some of you are walking around with bitterness in your spirit right now that's left over from something or someone that did something to you in your past.

41:27.752 --> 41:32.539
An ex-boss, an ex-spouse, an ex-friend, an ex-somebody.

41:32.919 --> 41:36.724
And it's still carrying around in your spirit, in your soul.

41:36.944 --> 41:39.207
And God wants to set you free from that.

41:39.989 --> 41:44.114
He does not want you walking around with this sense of bitterness and anger in your soul.

41:44.962 --> 41:49.731
Here's the thing that I think, ah, Holy Spirit, if you could help us grab onto this and actually take it.

41:50.052 --> 42:01.413
Whenever I experience tension in a relationship, the Holy Spirit is inviting me to grow, to become more like Him and to receive His power to respond in the way that He wants me to respond.

42:01.774 --> 42:04.018
See, when there's tension between Mary and I,

42:04.354 --> 42:14.973
I can either focus in on Mary and wish that she would do something different or be something different or I can ask Holy Spirit, what are you trying to teach me in this moment?

42:16.295 --> 42:24.430
If there's tension between me and a co-worker, I can either get mad at them or I can flip that and say, Holy Spirit, what do you want to teach me in this moment?

42:24.690 --> 42:26.734
Now, I know that's backwards, friends.

42:26.854 --> 42:27.495
I get that.

42:27.836 --> 42:28.978
But here's the thing.

42:29.186 --> 42:34.674
If I'm actually going to trust the engineer, then what I have to trust him with is that he's trying to teach me.

42:34.995 --> 42:36.817
He's trying to do something inside of me.

42:37.178 --> 42:51.680
And what happens is that we focus so often on the other person, and that just causes us to become more and more angry and bitter when there's actually an invitation on the table from God himself to the power of Holy Spirit to say, can I teach you in this moment?

42:53.643 --> 42:55.826
Can I teach you in this moment?

42:57.058 --> 43:04.505
Will you allow me to teach you what I want to teach you about being patient, about being forgiving?

43:06.046 --> 43:08.168
And I just got to say, I need this as much as anyone.

43:08.188 --> 43:11.231
There's not a person in this room who needs to hear this much as more than I do.

43:12.232 --> 43:14.554
There's invitations on the table.

43:15.395 --> 43:17.477
Now, there may be boundaries that we need to set up.

43:19.359 --> 43:21.481
Maybe the person's being abusive.

43:21.521 --> 43:26.866
And I'll just say this, if you're being abused in a relationship, then get out now.

43:27.938 --> 43:28.699
Get out now.

43:28.899 --> 43:32.063
If you're being abused, get out now.

43:34.046 --> 43:43.397
But if there's relationship tension, then allow Holy Spirit to do His work inside of you first.

43:46.521 --> 43:53.430
Allow Him to say, hey, there may be things Holy Spirit would whisper into our spirits.

43:53.630 --> 43:56.113
There may be things that I need to do in the other person's life.

43:56.313 --> 43:56.754
Yes.

43:57.922 --> 44:06.213
But the invitation on the table for you is where you allow me to do the things I want to do inside of you in this moment.

44:08.436 --> 44:15.726
You're so concerned about where the blame is going that they're 90% responsible, you're 10% responsible.

44:16.026 --> 44:24.137
And God is saying to us, but you're 100% responsible for responding to my Holy Spirit right now and what I'm wanting to teach you.

44:26.641 --> 44:27.602
That is so.

44:29.986 --> 44:31.167
Look at this passage of Scripture.

44:31.248 --> 44:32.789
With this, we're going to land the plane.

44:32.829 --> 44:36.974
I'm going to ask in just a moment, Josh, to come up and pray for us.

44:36.994 --> 44:47.948
As God's chosen people, holy and dearly loved by God, clothe yourself with compassion and kindness, humility, gentleness, and patience.

44:47.968 --> 44:57.059
Clothe yourself with compassion, kindness, humility, and gentleness, and patience.

44:57.799 --> 44:59.922
Bear with each other and forgive one another.

45:00.674 --> 45:04.119
If any of you has a grievance against someone, just forgive them.

45:04.739 --> 45:07.002
Forgive as the Lord forgave you.

45:07.043 --> 45:12.890
And over all these virtues put on love, which binds them all together in perfect unity.

45:14.092 --> 45:18.979
So, think about the tension you've got with some relationship in your life.

45:21.642 --> 45:27.570
What is the Holy Spirit inviting you into and saying to you,

45:29.698 --> 45:31.921
Will you let me do my work inside of you?

45:33.083 --> 45:34.004
Now here's the thing.

45:35.527 --> 45:40.474
You took the time to get about a bed, to get all ready, to get dressed and come here.

45:40.594 --> 45:42.357
I don't see anybody in their pajamas this morning.

45:42.397 --> 45:43.859
Congratulations, way to go.

45:45.442 --> 45:56.498
If you came this morning, can I encourage you to not just leave, to sing some songs, to laugh a little bit at a song, and then walk out those doors, the exact people that you walked in.

45:57.346 --> 46:00.930
Holy Spirit wants to meet with you in this space and in this time.

46:02.811 --> 46:19.187
Maybe over the area of your sexuality, maybe he's calling you to a different life as it relates to your sexuality, to put him first in that area of your life.

46:19.207 --> 46:26.034
Maybe he's calling you to redefinition of what it looks like to be

46:26.914 --> 46:29.398
his person in those relationships that are difficult.

46:31.361 --> 46:38.411
Maybe there's an invitation on the table for you, and instead of being so focused on the other person, you say, Holy Spirit, what do you want to say to me?

46:39.493 --> 46:40.294
Josh, would you come?

46:41.917 --> 46:42.858
So would you do me a favor?

46:43.659 --> 46:44.581
Just bow your heads.

46:45.362 --> 46:48.106
Again, I want you to know there's all kinds of love and there's forgiveness.

46:48.126 --> 46:49.328
This is a place of grace.

46:50.129 --> 46:52.873
This is a place of new beginnings.

46:53.654 --> 46:56.178
Absolutely do not condemn

46:56.354 --> 47:05.166
yourself, God is not a God who condemns, but he invites us in to new levels of understanding with him.

47:05.186 --> 47:07.449
And Josh is going to pray us through that in the next few minutes.

47:08.250 --> 47:08.530
Josh.

47:14.418 --> 47:18.884
Lord, we just thank you so much for your love and your grace.

47:19.245 --> 47:26.194
And in fact, kind of as a framing for this moment, I want to read from Romans eight.

47:26.338 --> 47:36.818
over us and I want to just encourage the body to receive this where it says that I am convinced that nothing can ever separate us from God's love.

47:36.838 --> 47:43.491
Neither death nor life, neither angels nor demons, neither our fears for today nor our worries about tomorrow.

47:44.713 --> 47:47.378
Not even the powers of hell can separate us from God's love.

47:48.354 --> 47:51.017
no power in the sky above or in the earth below.

47:51.057 --> 47:58.545
Indeed, nothing in all creation will ever be able to separate us from the love of God that is revealed in Christ Jesus our Lord.

48:02.350 --> 48:13.202
And we frame Lord this moment of reflection and prayer around that reminder because when

48:14.338 --> 48:27.396
When we get into things like relationship and conflict and sexual brokenness, it is so incredibly easy to just be buried by shame.

48:29.900 --> 48:31.963
And that is not your heart today for us.

48:34.847 --> 48:42.898
If there's any brokenness in our past, any sexual brokenness, any relational brokenness,

48:44.322 --> 48:49.768
It is not your intent for us to be buried in shame.

48:53.112 --> 49:00.501
It's your intent for us to recognize the love, the profound, everlasting, unfailing love that you have for each one of us.

49:02.103 --> 49:11.474
And for us to begin to dig and pursue and chase towards freedom, the freedom that you have for us, for wholeness.

49:14.178 --> 49:22.969
And so Lord, I would just ask, everybody that's in this room today, we bring different things to the table, relationally speaking.

49:27.034 --> 49:30.339
There's just such a wide variety of things that could be going on.

49:30.419 --> 49:42.514
And Holy Spirit, I just ask in this moment that you, in the heart of each individual, each person that's interacting with you right now that you would bring to light

49:43.138 --> 49:52.750
those things that we need to lift to you for redemption or wholeness or forgiveness, a reframing maybe.

49:54.833 --> 50:03.504
I love what Pastor Chris said about when we enter into conflict with another human being so often we concentrate on hoping that they change.

50:04.265 --> 50:11.794
Lord, change their heart and to spin that question on ourselves and to ask, Lord,

50:12.034 --> 50:13.295
What am I learning in this?

50:14.357 --> 50:17.560
Who are you making me into through this conflict?

50:18.621 --> 50:20.243
Who are you shaping me into?

50:20.343 --> 50:22.526
How can I be more like you?

50:22.566 --> 50:40.626
And so Lord, I just ask that you in this moment would just help us connect to the wisdom found in the scriptures to put on those pieces of clothing of humility and love and kindness and compassion.

50:42.146 --> 50:47.214
and that you would help us pursue wholeness and healing and love.

50:51.059 --> 50:57.749
We're about ready to sing a couple of songs that remind us of the love that you had for us.

50:59.251 --> 51:11.730
We're about ready to sing a song about how you pursued us, that you even did some things that would have been considered reckless in order to bring us back

51:12.322 --> 51:14.684
into a whole relationship with you.

51:16.746 --> 51:37.026
And so Lord, as we sing these songs, as we reflect upon your love, I would just ask that you would allow that love to just pour out on this place that we would be so filled up that it would just spill over and would have significant ripple and impact on the relationships that we have in our lives.

51:38.868 --> 51:40.690
That we would hand our shame and guilt to you.

51:41.922 --> 51:44.785
and step fully in the love and freedom that you have for us.

51:47.969 --> 51:50.131
Jesus, we love you.

51:50.151 --> 51:50.772
You're the best.

51:52.294 --> 51:55.297
And we pray all these things in your name.

51:56.298 --> 51:57.700
Amen, amen.

51:57.780 --> 52:05.569
Let's continue to worship.

52:05.589 --> 52:10.354
I won't forget the wonder of how you brought

52:11.714 --> 52:34.514
You're the God who fights for me, Lord of everything.

52:42.370 --> 53:10.674
You have torn apart the sea You have led me through the deep hallelujah hallelujah The cloud by day is the sign that You are with me The fire by night

53:11.522 --> 53:23.954
You found me, you found me You freed me, held back the waters from my release

01:01:12.834 --> 01:01:15.057
There is nothing that our God can't do.

01:01:15.377 --> 01:01:31.215
So glad that you have joined us today and hope today has been encouraging for you, that you have found great meaning in studying the Word, worshiping with us, praying along with us, and that has deepened your relationship with God and with others.

01:01:31.656 --> 01:01:36.882
We would love to continue to connect with you beyond this time that we've just had here.

01:01:37.122 --> 01:01:40.687
You can go to HeritageQC, slash connect at any point in time.

01:01:40.727 --> 01:01:52.103
You can fill out a connect card and that's a great way to get ahold of us if you want to talk to one of our pastors, if you want to sign up for a class or a group or just have any other kind of question that you're interested about in your own spiritual journey.

01:01:52.484 --> 01:01:56.149
You can also follow us on Instagram and Facebook.

01:01:56.169 --> 01:02:03.239
We have lots of great activities and different things that we post there to encourage you throughout your week along your spiritual journey as well.

01:02:03.839 --> 01:02:05.682
Also on HeritageQC.com,

01:02:05.762 --> 01:02:15.938
You can also give a great way to continue to support ministries just like this one to serve you and also the rest of the Quad City area and beyond.

01:02:16.459 --> 01:02:26.274
